      "lotl": {
        "label": "What's Going On With the Leafs",
        "body": "The curtain slammed shut on another Toronto Maple Leafs debacle - 32-36-14, a measly 78 points, eighth in the Atlantic and <strong>31 games behind the division leaders</strong>, capped by a soul-crushing L7 streak that left them 15th in the playoff seedings and eliminated before the tape even stopped rolling. What went wrong? The same old script: star power fizzling when it mattered, defensive sieves leaking 3.2 goals per game, and a power play that ranked 22nd league-wide, turning prime chances into punchlines. Mitch Marner's shadow looms large - the guy who bolted to Vegas last summer for a fresh start, now torching nets with three points in a Game 6 clincher against Utah, his 80-point regular season a reminder of what Toronto squandered. Craig Berube's bench bossing couldn't mask the rot; whispers of a coaching purge swirl already. Free agency hits with cap space burning a hole - target grit on the blue line, not another finesse forward. Draft lottery odds at 6.5 percent for a top pick offer slim hope. <strong>Watch the ping-pong balls Tuesday - they're this rebuild's first real lifeline</strong>.",
        "updated": "Updated May 3, 2026"
      },
