      "lotl": {
        "label": "What's Going On With the Jays",
        "body": "The Blue Jays are clawing back into the AL East hunt, refusing to fade quietly after a brutal April skid. <strong>An eight-run eighth-inning explosion Saturday - capped by Brandon Valenzuela's third big-league homer - fueled an 11-4 rout of the Twins, their second straight win after Friday's 7-3 triumph</strong>, flipping a 2-1 series lead and bumping them to 16-17, third in the division but a precarious six games back. Kazuma Okamoto's third homer in two days sizzled off the bat, while Vladimir Guerrero Jr. loomed large before Spencer Miles slammed the door in the ninth - no major injuries clouding this surge, just pure momentum. At 16-17 with playoff seed seven in sight, they're no juggernaut yet, but that two-game streak whispers contender grit. <strong>The rubber game awaits today at 11:45 AM ET in Minneapolis - Yesavage's pristine 1-0, 0.00 ERA versus Joe Ryan - where a sweep could ignite real belief before they bolt home</strong>.",
        "updated": "Updated May 3, 2026"
      },
