      "lotl": {
        "label": "What's Going On With the Raptors",
        "body": "<strong>The Raptors beat the Cavaliers 112-110</strong>, moving to 46-36 on the season. They currently sit 3rd in atlantic division, with every game now carrying real stakes for positioning. The win snaps what had been a fluky stretch and gets the group back on track heading into the next set of games. Prior to that, the club lost to the Cavaliers, 120-125, a game that gave the coaching staff real tape to work with. The playoff picture is the whole story now, so every lineup tweak, every matchup decision, every minute carries postseason weight. <strong>Next up: at Cavaliers on Sun 5/3 at 6:30 PM ET.</strong> Around the NBA, the offseason machinery is already whirring - front offices are mapping out draft boards, free-agent target lists are being quietly circulated, and cap projections are being stress-tested against every conceivable scenario. For the Toronto Raptors, the conversation centers on which direction the rebuild takes next and whether the draft lottery delivers the kind of franchise-altering talent that can accelerate the timeline.",
        "updated": "Updated May 3, 2026"
      },
