      "lotl": {
        "label": "What's Going On With the Commanders",
        "body": "The draft dust settles in Washington, and the Commanders - fresh off a 5-12 slog that left them third in the NFC East, six games back - emerged with a haul screaming rebuild under Dan Quinn's watchful eye. They snagged <strong>LSU cornerback Mansoor Delane in the first round</strong>, a DMV kid from Silver Spring who slipped to them after the Chiefs passed, his ball skills a scheme fit for Quinn's aggressive secondary that desperately needs lockdown coverage opposite a thin group. Round two brought Michigan linebacker Jaishawn Barham, the ex-Terp with 95 tackles and seven sacks in college, plugging holes behind an aging front seven - immediate depth with starter upside. Third-round steal: a gritty leader whose physicality bolsters the trenches. No undrafted gems yet, but the rookie class shifts the depth chart now, with Delane eyeing Week 1 snaps and Barham climbing fast. Whispers swirl of chasing ex-Cowboy Trevon Diggs to turbocharge that secondary - Quinn's old ties could make it real. <strong>OTAs next month will reveal if these pups ignite a leap from last year's wreckage - or if Quinn doubles down on vet corners first.</strong>",
        "updated": "Updated May 3, 2026"
      },
